.SH NAME
Test::Trap::Builder::PerlIO \- Capture strategy using PerlIO::scalar
.SH VERSION
.IX Header "VERSION"
Version 0.3.5
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module provides a capture strategy \fIperlio\fR, based on
PerlIO::scalar, for the trap's output layers.  Note that you may
specify different strategies for each output layer on the trap.
.PP
See also Test::Trap (:stdout and :stderr) and
Test::Trap::Builder (output_layer).
.SH CAVEATS
.IX Header "CAVEATS"
These layers use in-memory files, and so will not (indeed cannot) trap
output from forked-off processes \-\- including \fBsystem()\fR calls.
.PP
Threads?  No idea.  It might even work correctly.
